# SVG diagram uniformity

Use these conventions for all SVG diagrams in this repository.

## Mandatory grouping

- Every pictogram must be wrapped in its own `<g>` group.
- Every arrow must be wrapped in its own `<g>` group.
- Every block must be wrapped in its own `<g>` group containing:
  - block rectangle,
  - pictogram group,
  - text label.

## Block normalization

- Use a normalized block size across one diagram (same width and height for all standard blocks).
- Keep a consistent corner radius and stroke style for standard blocks.
- Reserve upper **2/3** of the block for the pictogram area.
- Reserve lower **1/3** of the block for the text label.
- Place the text inside the rectangle, centered in the lower third.

## Arrow normalization

- Use shared markers (arrow heads) from `<defs>`.
- Keep consistent stroke width and color semantics per diagram:
  - forward/main flow,
  - success/ack,
  - compensation/error.
- Do not leave free-floating arrow paths outside `<g>` wrappers.

## Icon consistency

- Use one icon stroke style per diagram family (line cap, line join, stroke width).
- Keep icon visual weight similar between blocks.
- Prefer simple geometric pictograms over detailed illustrations.

## Text and layout

- Use one typography system per diagram (`title`, `label`, optional `step` classes).
- Keep labels short and domain-driven.
- Do not place block labels outside block bounds.
